metadata.name: Dubious Floofs #41
metadata.description:
These little guys love to run around in grassy hills and meadows, but they can get easily distracted...

I designed this so that it will always fit to the height of your window. That means you can adjust the window width and refresh to uncover more of the terrain. Enjoy!

metadata.name: Zen(禅) #48
metadata.description:
"Zen(禅)" is an exploration to find peace and harmony in a modern work of art. Different color palettes along with the cultural and minimal elements of Chinese and Japanese paintings and their diverse arrangement creates an artwork that includes a wide range of color palettes from day to night colors.

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork.
Made with P5js.

metadata.name: Morixels Mans #1175
metadata.description:
The Morixels Mans is unique Random Generated 10,000 PFP NFTs, and this collection is for people like me who are nostalgic for pixel arts.
This collection is manually designed.
The original Artwork was designed in 24 by 24 pixels and then resized to 1080 by 1080 resolution. 
The number of Traits in this collection is 12 (120 layers) and it has the ability to make 31,091,558,400 NFTs.
Some ​layers are less than 1 percent of the total, some 100 percent, and some between 0.1 and 100 percent.
To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.
To Produce this collection, all the layers were designed pixel by pixel, which was time-consuming and difficult. And this greatly increases the value of this collection.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

Twitter: @Morixels

Website: https://morixels.com/

Designed by: @morteza_yousefy
Made in 2022

metadata.name: Canyon #81
metadata.description:
Canyon is a generative art project inspired by canyons and reinterpreted in 9 different styles (that each have their own specificities):
- Grand Canyon
- Radioactive
- Blue Grotto
- Black Crystals
- Magma
- Iceberg
- Imagination
- UV
- Sandstone

Accessories (Kayak, Rowing Boat, Barrels) are present on some variations (in this case, it is possible to generate a second variation without accessories by pressing "a").

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: The Voyage #40
metadata.description:
The more we explore, the more things we realize there are to be explored. The more questions we find answers to, the more answers we find that require the right questions to be asked.

What is there beyond the edge of knowledge; what was, when things were none?

Will it be our body or our mind to discover that first?

And so The Voyage begins...

* * *

Press R to hide/show cosmic rain (takes a few seconds).
Press S to save as PNG.

Made by: yenren / twitter.com/yenrenART
Made with: JavaScript + HTML Canvas
License: LICENSE.txt

metadata.name: Glomularus #54
metadata.description:
Glomularus is an exploration in generative, artificial life forms. The project is an extension of my Protobyte series, begun in 2004.

Driven by Verlet icosahedra and responsive tendrils, Glomulari live in a spherical virtual ecosystem (V-eco) enhanced through user interaction.

Interaction:

Mouse/Trackpad:
  drag -> camera rotation
  drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
  scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
  1-9: add acceleration
  -, +: reduce | increase V-eco sphere radius
  f, g: reduce | increase fog
  p: screen capture

Tip:
To decrease creature acceleration, reduce V-eco sphere radius

Note:
Please post your favorite Glomularus screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node
